article.headline: Mercer 89, Stetson 76
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- James Odoms scored 19 points to lead Mercer to a 89-76 win over Stetson in the Atlantic Sun Conference opener for both Thursday night. Odoms led five players in double figures for Mercer (3-1, 1-0), who matched last year's total with one conference road win. Will Emerson had 18 points and seven rebounds for the Bears and Wesley Duke added 17 points. Jacob Skogen also had 15 points for Mercer while Ross Alacqua added 12 points off the bench. The Bears trailed only after E.J. Gordon's basket opened the scoring. After a jumper by Emerson tied it at 2, Stetson never led again. Mercer hit 12-of-28 shots from behind the arc while Stetson hit just five 3-pointers on the night. Stetson trailed 37-33 at the half and got within two points when Borislav Djordjic opened the second-half with a layup, but that was as close as Stetson got the rest of the way. Djordjic and Karl Hollingsworth each scored 14 points to lead the Hatters.
